On Sun, 24 Dec 2006, Ryan Hink wrote:

> Only a week ago I installed 2 of the 3" Atwood blowers in the engine
> compartment. I mounted them to the ceiling on each side and extended the
> heater hoses from the doghouse.

Since you're doing all this replumbing, why not create a vent behind the
spare tire (like the ones on the gas heater equipped buses) and plumb this
to the inlet of your bilge blowers?  That way you get recirculation.
